revision.text:
{{also|Polish}}
==English==

===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*pel- (beat)}}
From {{inh|en|enm|polishen}}, from {{der|en|fro|-}} ''poliss-'', stem of some of the conjugated forms of {{m|fro|polir}}, from {{der|en|la|polio|polīre|to polish, make smooth}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*pelh₂-||to drive, strike, thrust}}, from the notion of fulling cloth.

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|pŏl'ĭsh|a=UK}}, {{IPA|en|/ˈpɒl.ɪʃ/}}
* {{enPR|pä'lĭsh|a=US}}, {{IPA|en|/ˈpɑ.lɪʃ/}}
* {{audio|en|en-us-polish.ogg|a=US}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# A [[substance]] used to polish.
#: {{ux|en|A good silver '''polish''' will remove tarnish easily.}}
# [[cleanliness|Cleanliness]]; smoothness, shininess.
#: {{ux|en|The floor was waxed to a high '''polish'''.}}
# [[refinement|Refinement]]; cleanliness in performance or presentation.
#: {{ux|en|The lecturer showed a lot of '''polish''' at his last talk.}}

